## Environment Variables

Display all variables

```bash
printenv
```

or

```bash
env
```

Display one variable

```bash
echo $HOME
```

Create variable

```bash
MYVAR="Hello"
```

Export variable

```bash
export MYVAR
```

---

## Process Management

View processes

```bash
ps
```

Monitor processes

```bash
top
```

Display process tree

```bash
pstree
```

---

## Background & Foreground Jobs

Run in background

```bash
command &
```

Suspend process

```
Ctrl + Z
```

Resume in background

```bash
bg
```

Resume in foreground

```bash
fg
```

List jobs

```bash
jobs
```

---

## Killing Processes

Graceful termination

```bash
kill PID
```

Force kill

```bash
kill -9 PID
```

Display signals

```bash
kill -l
```

---

## Exit Status

Display previous command status

```bash
echo $?
```

Exit script

```bash
exit
```

